From: nix-wasm <eric@codebutler.com>
Subject: [PATCH] wasm: enlarge user stack 8KiB->4MiB (binfmt_wasm)

The 8 KiB user stack overflowed on a single musl realpath() call and crashed
nix at startup. NOMMU stacks cannot grow; size it to 4 MiB (the alloc rounds
to an available 8 MiB/order-11 block; a full 8 MiB stack would need a
nonexistent 16 MiB/order-12 block and fail with ENOMEM).

--- a/fs/binfmt_wasm.c
+++ b/fs/binfmt_wasm.c
@@ -20,7 +20,17 @@
 #include <linux/uaccess.h>
 #include <linux/vmalloc.h>
 
-#define WASM_STACK_SIZE		(2UL * PAGE_SIZE)
+/*
+ * User stack (shares this region with brk; musl mallocng uses mmap not brk, so
+ * it is effectively the stack). NOMMU stacks can't grow on fault -> HARD ceiling.
+ * The original 2 pages (8 KiB) overflowed on a single musl realpath() call
+ * (char stack[PATH_MAX+1] + char output[PATH_MAX] = 8 KiB) and crashed nix
+ * (deep C++/std::filesystem stacks). Use 4 MiB: big enough for realpath/nix, and (with the arg extra) the
+ * NOMMU power-of-2 mmap rounds to an 8 MiB/order-11 block, which the buddy
+ * allocator has free (a full 8 MiB stack rounds to order-12/16 MiB, of which
+ * there are none → ENOMEM at exec).
+ */
+#define WASM_STACK_SIZE		(1024UL * PAGE_SIZE)
 
 /*
